"To hurt a man who's always been with me since I was born is the pain that's been with me for the rest of her life," she said.
This case is likely to be a legal precedent, since Massachusetts does not have a law that provides for the responsibility of advising a person to commit suicide.
In 2014, when Roy was found dead in a car with symptoms of carbon monoxide poisoning, Carter was 17 years old.
