"You can hang yourself, jump off the roof, stab yourself with a knife, I don't know many ways," she wrote in a few messages sent two weeks before he died while he was resting with his family.
A few minutes before she committed suicide, she wrote, "You have to do this, Conrad" and "You only have to turn on the ignition, and you're going to be free and happy."
Judge Monis said that Carter wanted to get attention through Roy's death, and he prohibited her from communicating with the press to prevent her from getting what she wanted.
