“If you are going to ask for 4,000 proposals, you should be prepared to hold 4,000 interviews,” says Russell Rat, president of the management consulting firm Kotter International, who had to see companies make a mistake by relying too much on data collection.
"Because if you don't go to the end, the staff will say, "Did you really hear me?
