The Federal Antimonopoly Service of the country, in accordance with the Decision of the Government of the Russian Federation on the amendment of the wholesale electricity and power market regulations and in the consolidated forecast balance between the production and supply of electricity (power) within the framework of the unified energy system of the Russian Federation for the constituent entities of the Russian Federation (No. 842), has established indicative prices for electricity and power for industrial consumers of the Republic of Buryat.
As a result, the cost of electricity for drilling producers is reduced by a quarter, making life easier for small and medium-sized enterprises and individual entrepreneurs.
For many decades, the leaders of the Republic have beaten the thresholds of the Moscow Cabinets in futile attempts to equalize the region in tariffs with the neighbouring Irkutsk region with that of the Angar hydropower cartridge emanating from Baikal, the main catchment area of which is Buryatia.
And it's not until this year that progress has begun.
In March, the electricity tariffs for the population of the Republic were reduced from rouble 4.24 per cent to rouK 3.93 per cent, or 7.3 per cent.
With the inclusion of Buryatia by decision of the Federal Government in the list of areas of value areas of the wholesale market for which the operation of the wholesale and retail markets has been determined, industrial consumers have moved forward.
