According to the representative of Pladis, “the head of the Tokros facility only yesterday received a letter from the GMB Scotland branch, and the company will respond immediately, as we appreciate our continued cooperation with the staff and representatives of the trade union”.
Two months ago, we held a regular meeting in Tokros with staff and representatives of the GMB, at which a number of issues were openly discussed.
We talked to staff about how, as all companies operating in the most competitive and unstable economic environment, we are constantly reviewing our actions – and this applies to all our facilities and activities – to remain competitive.
