In Ukraine, Russian prisoners were asked to be sent to prison for illegal border crossing
The Supreme Council of Ukraine has registered a draft law according to which criminal penalties may be imposed on Russians for illegal crossing of the Ukrainian border.
According to the TV channel RT, the document recorded in the electronic database of the Ukrainian Parliament provides for a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens attempting to enter the country illegally.
It is noted that for a repeat offence or act committed by a group of persons, the sentence may be extended to five years.
If, however, the perpetrator was detained at the border with weapons, the period of detention for him would increase to eight years.
